leadingComments.value: check if data contains ID3 timestamp and MPEG sync word
Look for MPEG header | 1111 1111 | 111X XYZX | where X can be either 0 or 1 and Y or Z should be 1
Layer bits (position 14 and 15) in header should be always different from 0 (Layer I or Layer II or Layer III)

trailingComments.value: feed incoming data to the front of the parsing pipeline

leadingComments.value: logger.log('Unable to parse Mpeg audio frame');
